The game was a charity exhibition between the Giants and the Yankees at the Polo Grounds on April 21, 1912, and raised more than $9,000. Giants won 11-2. The article states:

&quot;There were a few side features. George M. Cohan gave an imitation of a newsboy selling papers and a number of girls went among the spectators for donations. They called themselves the female Giants, but they were all featherweights.&quot;
